n Belgium as of June 8th, religious ceremonies may be resumed subject to the following: 

-Safety distances must be observed with a maximum of 100 persons;
-As of July, this number will be increased to 200, just like in the cultural and sports industries;
-Rituals with physical contact are still not allowed.

3 June: From 8 June, non-contact sports activities can be resumed, both indoor and outdoor, amateur or professional, league and training. Gyms and fitness rooms may also be reopened, subject to protocol.
However:
Contact sports (e.g. judo, boxing, football, etc.) should always be limited to “contactless” training;

Belgium, 23 July: The National Security Council has adopted a series of measures that will apply across the country from Saturday, July 25.

In addition to the current obligations, wearing a mouth mask will also be mandatory :
- At markets, flea markets and fairs ,

- In shopping streets and in all busy places (private or public) as determined by the local authorities;

- In all public buildings for the parts that are accessible to the public;

- In catering establishments , except when people are sitting at the table;
